---
// Bridge — from problem to promise. Every headline reframed as what the product is
// designed to do (and what's implemented), not as what customers have already achieved.
---
<section id="product" class="relative bg-surface-50 py-24 md:py-32 overflow-hidden">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
    <p class="eyebrow reveal">Here is what changes on Monday</p>
    <h2 class="mt-3 text-h1 font-bold text-navy-900 reveal">
      You open <span class="gradient-amber">one tab.</span><br/>
      The AI opens everything else.
    </h2>

    <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-navy-900/75 max-w-prose reveal">
      LogisticsPrizm is a purpose-built TMS for mid-market freight forwarders, 3PLs, NVOCCs, and customs brokers.
      Quote generation, live tracking, invoice reconciliation, compliance screening, and financials —
      one platform, one data model, one monthly bill.
      <strong class="text-navy-900">No implementation partners. No add-on modules. No surprises at renewal.</strong>
    </p>

    <div class="mt-14 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 reveal">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-7 shadow-sm">
        <div class="font-mono text-xs text-prizm-600 tracking-widest uppercase">01 · Quote</div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-2xl font-bold text-navy-900">Under a minute, not six hours.</div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-navy-900/70">The engine reads your historical rates, pulls live carrier pricing,
          applies the right surcharges, and drafts a quote your rep can review — while they&#39;re still reading the RFQ.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-7 shadow-sm">
        <div class="font-mono text-xs text-prizm-600 tracking-widest uppercase">02 · Track</div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-2xl font-bold text-navy-900">Every milestone, every mode.</div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-navy-900/70">Ocean, air, rail, road, intermodal. Carrier webhook and polling adapters normalize into
          one event stream. The customer portal shows the same truth your ops team sees.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-7 shadow-sm">
        <div class="font-mono text-xs text-prizm-600 tracking-widest uppercase">03 · Recover</div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-2xl font-bold text-navy-900">Invoice leakage, flagged.</div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-navy-900/70">Every carrier invoice is matched line-by-line against the quote and your rate card.
          Variance above the threshold is flagged before the invoice is paid.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
